r election purposes serving as polling stations, a move that could be called politicizing schools just as these protesters claim schools are being turned into mosques by allowing Friday prayers. &#10;The community can build its own prayer facility for kids without raising bad feelings about turning the educational facility into a religious centre as falsely claimed by some. In any event, it is a good thing if kids' spiritual needs are addressed by all parties in a non-confrontational way. &#10;The protesters can benefit by a course in comparative religion, which the school can organize for adults. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="896" language="en" documentId="1335" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="santron" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1335" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="33"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="34" end="274"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="275" end="494"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="495" end="789"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="790" end="896"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55"/></xmi:XMI>